        <h1>Temporary closure of North Greenwich Bus Station for essential works</h1>
        <div class="content-page-press-release">
        30 July 2013
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        North Greenwich bus station will be closed for approximately four weeks from Saturday 3 August while essential works are carried out.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<p>This will temporarily affect where you catch your bus, the position of the taxi rank and disabled parking near to the bus station.</p>
<p>The decision to close the station, which handles over 30,000 passengers on a typical weekday, followed careful consideration by Transport for London (TfL) to minimise inconvenience for passengers and take advantage of reduced passenger numbers during the school holidays - a period where fewer events are taking place at the nearby O2 Arena.</p>
<p>The bus station will receive extensive repairs to the access road surfaces and improvements to the drainage system which will help minimise any future inconvenience from potential closures.&nbsp; </p>
<p>During the closure changes will also be made to the pedestrian crossings designed to improve passenger safety. </p>
<h2>Relocated taxi rank</h2>
<p>During these works bus routes 108, 129, 132, 161, 188, 422, 472 and 486 will use nearby stops F and G on Millennium Way.</p>
<p>Full details of the stopping arrangements will be displayed throughout the bus station and on the website <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk">www.tfl.gov.uk</a>.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Bus station staff will also be available to advise passengers of where to catch their bus. </p>
<p>The taxi rank will be relocated from its current location to a temporary pick up area adjacent to East Parkside.&nbsp;</p>
<p>These changes will take effect from Monday 5 August until the completion of the works.&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Blue Badge</h2>
<p>Directional signage will be displayed to assist passengers.</p>
<p>The disabled parking in the NCP car park behind the bus station will also be relocated during these works.</p>
<p>During this time Blue Badge holders will be able to park in the North Greenwich Underground station main car park located in Edmund Halley Way.&nbsp; </p>
<p>Bays conveniently placed closest to the bus and the London Underground station will be widened to provide fully accessible parking.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>

     

        
        
        
